==English==

===Etymology===
From French [[cabale]] from Medieval Latin [[cabala]] from which [[Kabbalah]] is also derived. It is likely that the mystical often secrative nature of Kabbalah led to formation of the word cabal.

===Pronunciation===
'''IPA''': kɐbaɫ

